 Show that the two triangles in the diagram above are
    similar.  Use this to show that
    $$
    y\dx{y}=-x\dx{x}.
    $$
    \comment{Notice that this problem specifically asks you to use the
      triangles, not differentiation to show that
      $y\dx{y}=-x\dx{x}.$}
  </p>
</statement>
