<task>
<statement>
<p>
 After Problem~\#\ref{problem:dydxIsSlope} we observed that the
    ratio $\dfdx{y}{x}$ must represent the slope of both the curve
    and its tangent line at a given point.

    Notice that the differential equation for the circle can be
    written as
    $$
    \dfdx{y}{x}=-\frac{x}{y}.
    $$
    Explain how this is related to the geometric fact that the tangent
    to a circle at a point is perpendicular to the radius through that
    point.
  </p>
